    <item>
      <title>My year in photos (2023)</title>
      <link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2023/my-year-in-photos-2023/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 31 Dec 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2023/my-year-in-photos-2023/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;2023 has been a stressful and hard year, and I have a sneaking suspicion this is a preview of even harder years on my path ahead.  I am finding myself more tired and having really poor sleep quality, and I&amp;rsquo;m not sure I see things improving but I am cautiously optimisitic.  I&amp;rsquo;ve been trying to keep positive by remembering my blessings as best I can, and this year came with a lot of blessings for sure.  This post I do yearly forces me to acknowledge those blessings.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Video: Spring in Kyoto Revisited</title>
      <link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2020/video-spring-in-kyoto-revisited/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Jan 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2020/video-spring-in-kyoto-revisited/</guid>
      <description>&lt;!-- &lt;video controls preload=&#34;metadata&#34; poster=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/videos/spring-in-kyoto.jpg&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;source src=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/videos/spring-in-kyoto.mp4&#34; type=&#34;video/mp4&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#x9;Your browser does not support the HTML5 video tag.&#xA;&lt;/video&gt; --&gt;&#xA;&lt;iframe src=&#34;https://player.vimeo.com/video/586932947?h=c67825fca3&#34; width=&#34;640&#34; height=&#34;360&#34; frameborder=&#34;0&#34; allow=&#34;autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture&#34; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A while back I posted an &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2013/video-spring-in-kyoto-%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E3%81%AE%E6%98%A5/&#34;&gt;old video I made of Spring in Kyoto&lt;/a&gt;, but the audio track was removed by YouTube. So I&amp;rsquo;m self-hosting it here now, and reposting to revisit the memories!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I really enjoy the atmosphere in this video, and I wish I made more videos like them. I used my Canon 7D for a lot of the video, but I wish it was shot in RAW video and on a tripod, as a lot of the detail was lost and a lot of the video ended up &amp;ldquo;wobbly&amp;rdquo;. There is also some software stabilization which looks pretty unnatural.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
