content=&#34;true&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;source type=&#34;image/webp&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 500px)&#34; srcset=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/kyoto-kitano-tenmangu/20190214-5D__2616-500px-resize.webp&#34; /&gt;&#xA;        &lt;source type=&#34;image/webp&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 1000px)&#34; srcset=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/kyoto-kitano-tenmangu/20190214-5D__2616-1000px-resize.webp&#34; /&gt;&#xA;        &lt;source type=&#34;image/webp&#34; media=&#34;(min-width: 1001px)&#34; srcset=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/kyoto-kitano-tenmangu/20190214-5D__2616-2000px-resize.webp&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;source type=&#34;image/jpeg&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 500px)&#34; srcset=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/kyoto-kitano-tenmangu/20190214-5D__2616-500px-resize.jpeg&#34; /&gt;&#xA;        &lt;source type=&#34;image/jpeg&#34; media=&#34;(max-width: 1000px)&#34; srcset=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/kyoto-kitano-tenmangu/20190214-5D__2616-1000px-resize.jpeg&#34; /&gt;&#xA;        &lt;source type=&#34;image/jpeg&#34; media=&#34;(min-width: 1001px)&#34; srcset=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/kyoto-kitano-tenmangu/20190214-5D__2616-2000px-resize.jpeg&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&#xA;        &lt;img data-foo=&#34;2&#34; itemprop=&#34;url&#34; src=&#34;https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/kyoto-kitano-tenmangu/20190214-5D__2616-2000px-resize.jpeg&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; width=&#34;2000&#34; height=&#34;1333&#34; style=&#34;aspect-ratio: 2000 / 1333;&#34;  /&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;The roof of the main shrine (拝殿) at Kitano Tenmangu.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;p&gt;Almost a year ago now I was lucky to be able to go back to my old stomping grounds in Kyoto, where I once studied Japanese in the hopes of maybe learning enough of the language to enroll in a university there to continue my studies in philosophy, perhaps being able to one day be another &amp;ldquo;professional&amp;rdquo; philosopher to walk along the &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosopher%27s_Walk&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;Philosopher&amp;#39;s Path&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>My year in photos (2019)</title>
      <link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2019/my-year-in-photos-2019/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 31 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2019/my-year-in-photos-2019/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In many ways this has been a strange and wonderful year, probably my most favorite year of my life to date.  I traveled to Japan on a great flight deal, I hiked more than 1100 miles of the Appalachian Trail, and I drove across the USA on two (!) cross-country road trips, the latter a wonderful solo trip where I took my time photographing and visiting wonderful parks and museums.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>My year in photos (2016)</title>
      <link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2016/my-year-in-photos-2016/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 31 Dec 2016 23:17:16 -0800</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2016/my-year-in-photos-2016/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A few years back I put together my favorite photos of the year (see it: &lt;a href=&#34;//davidbcalhoun.com/2014/my-year-in-photos-2014/&#34;&gt;part one&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;//davidbcalhoun.com/2014/my-year-in-photos-2014-part-2/&#34;&gt;part two&lt;/a&gt;).  I decided to resurrect the tradition, and I hope to keep it going in the coming years!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Onto the pics!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;february&#34;&gt;February&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I visited Yosemite twice, first by myself and later with my friend Kevin.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure itemprop=&#34;image&#34; itemscope=&#34;&#34; itemtype=&#34;http://schema.org/ImageObject&#34; class=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;meta itemprop=&#34;width&#34; content=&#34;1500&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;meta itemprop=&#34;height&#34; content=&#34;1000&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;meta itemprop=&#34;url&#34; content=&#34;http://davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/2016-best-of-01-feb-yosemite-night-sky.jpg&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;img itemprop=&#34;contentUrl&#34; src=&#34;http://davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/2016-best-of-01-feb-yosemite-night-sky.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Night sky from Yosemite&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;figcaption itemprop=&#34;caption&#34;&gt;Night sky from Yosemite&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For this shot I drove to the empty Bridalveil Falls parking lot and placed an LED lantern in the middle of the parking lot, then shot straight up.  I was super happy with the way this turned out.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Photo assignment: Kyoto alleyways at night</title>
      <link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2016/photo-assignment-kyoto-alleyways-at-night/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 14 Jun 2016 22:15:52 +0900</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2016/photo-assignment-kyoto-alleyways-at-night/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Before setting off on my current trip, I wanted to give myself at least one &amp;ldquo;photo assignment&amp;rdquo;: some goal I could aim to accomplish by pretending like I&amp;rsquo;d been given an assignment by some employer.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is the first of what I hope will be many.  The assignment here is to try to capture the atmosphere of eastern Kyoto&amp;rsquo;s traditional streets at night.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A couple of things I had to plan for: Kyoto is a bit far from my hostel in Osaka, so I made sure to make a day trip out of it.  Also, I wanted preferably a somewhat rainy day, which would make the ground more reflective.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Kyoto Cherry Blossoms 2013 (京都の桜２０１３年)</title>
      <link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2013/kyoto-cherry-blossoms-2013-%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E3%81%AE%E6%A1%9C%EF%BC%92%EF%BC%90%EF%BC%91%EF%BC%93%E5%B9%B4/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 30 Apr 2013 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2013/kyoto-cherry-blossoms-2013-%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E3%81%AE%E6%A1%9C%EF%BC%92%EF%BC%90%EF%BC%91%EF%BC%93%E5%B9%B4/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure itemprop=&#34;image&#34; itemscope=&#34;&#34; itemtype=&#34;http://schema.org/ImageObject&#34; class=&#34;center&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;meta itemprop=&#34;width&#34; content=&#34;3006&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;meta itemprop=&#34;height&#34; content=&#34;2004&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;meta itemprop=&#34;url&#34; content=&#34;http://davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/cherry-blossoms-kyoto-japan-IMG_3207.jpg&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.flickr.com/photos/franksvalli/8691586416/&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &#x9;&lt;img itemprop=&#34;contentUrl&#34; src=&#34;http://davidbcalhoun.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/cherry-blossoms-kyoto-japan-IMG_3207.jpg&#34; title=&#34;Cherry blossoms in Kyoto, Japan 2013&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&#x9;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;figcaption itemprop=&#34;caption&#34;&gt;Cherry blossoms in Kyoto, Japan 2013&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.flickr.com/photos/franksvalli/sets/72157633239996237/&#34;&gt;Check out my cherry blossoms 2013 set on Flickr.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Japan has a healthy fascination with the beauty of nature, and this includes the ephemeral cherry blossoms. And one of the prime locations for cherry blossoms is Kyoto, Japan.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It takes a while to realize, but there actually seems to be a wide variety of cherry blossoms which blossom at different times. This stretches the season out a bit (the prime blossoming lasts only about a week). It&amp;rsquo;s nice to be able to walk around for a few weeks and find random beautiful cherry blossoms.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
